:s/<text_pattern>/<replace_text>/       Only replace text in current line
:%s/<text_pattern>/<replace_text>/      Search and replace first instance of text
:%s/<text_pattern>/<replace_text>/g     Search and replace all instance of text
:%s//<replace_text>/                    If you leave text blank vim will replace using last searched item
r<string>                               Will replace the character under the cursor with string
gUis                                    Make current sentence upper case